SIMPLE: supralapsarian
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Supralapsarian
<hw>Su`pra*lap*sa"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Supra-</ets> + <ets>lapse</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>supralapsaire</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One of
that class of Calvinists who believed that God's decree of election
determined that man should fall, in order that the opportunity might be
furnished of securing the redemption of a part of the race, the decree
of salvation being conceived of as formed <xex>before</xex> or
<xex>beyond</xex>, and not <xex>after</xex> or <xex>following</xex>, the
lapse, or fall. Cf. <er>Infralapsarian</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supralapsarian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Supralapsarian
<hw>Su`pra*lap*sa"ri*an</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to the
Supralapsarians, or their doctrine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Supralapsarianism</ent>⟦br⟧
